Lee COPHER, Appellant,
v.
POPEYES LOUISIANA KITCHEN INC., Respondent, ARC CafeUSA001, LLC and Amber Tillman, Defendants. No. ED 106268 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION THREE. Filed: December 11, 2018 Timothy J. Phillips, 305 Main St., St. Louis, MO 63026, for appellant. Brandan P. Mueller, 190 Carondelet Plaza, Suite 600, St. Louis, MO 63105, Thomas B. Weaver, Cynthia M. Juedemann, 7700 Forsyth Blvd., Suite 1800, St. Luis, MO 63105, for respondent. Before Sherri B. Sullivan, P.J., Lawrence E. Mooney, J., and James M. Dowd, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

Lee Copher appeals the circuit court's judgment setting aside a default judgment entered in his favor against Popeyes Louisiana Kitchen, Inc. An opinion would have no precedential value. We have furnished the parties with a memorandum, for their information only, setting forth the reasons for this order. We affirm. Rule 84.16(b)(5).
